<a name="#contentValidation"></a>
<p class="uportal-channel-strong">How do I configure the portlet to allow content validation before submission ?</p>
<p>By default, the portlet scans the submitted content for cross-site security issues  using the OWASP AntiSamy package. Issues are reported back to the user and submission is cancelled if any are found. To change this behavior,
go to the Preferences page of the portlet and add/modify the setting for "xss.validation.enabled". The portlet will use the value assigned to this field to determine whether or not content should be scanned. 

If you wish to alter the rules that define cross-site scripting vulnerabilities for the portlet, please adjust the rules defined in the "antiSammyPolicy.xml" file. 
</p>
